<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="17Oct1935"><font color="red">17 October 1935</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Lucia Joyce): Se la tua fotografia &egrave; un indice del tuo stato di salute devi stare molto, ma molto meglio. Ed ora, cara Lucia, devi diventare ogni d&igrave; in ogni modo&mdash;insomma suona male in italiano ma &egrave; quello che predica il revenendissimo e sapientissimo dottore Cou&eacute;. <br>Translation: If your photgraph is indicative of your state of health you must be much, much better. And now, dear Lucia, every day in every way you have to become&mdash;this doesn't sound right in Italian but it is what the most reverend and most wise Dr Cou&eacute; preaches. </div>
